        "title": "How can I use IntStream.range with map to create a new List from a pre-existing List. This is just for research purposes",
        "body": "<p>I have an initial Integer List ('''numbers = List.of(2,2,4,6,8,243,11,17,19);''') and I wanted to attempt to carry out a Functional Program to take the first 5 numbers from <em><strong>numbers<\/strong><\/em>, square them then put them in a new List.<\/p>\n<p>I know how to create new odd and even lists from <em><strong>numbers<\/strong><\/em>:<\/p>\n<pre><code>private static List&lt;Integer&gt; createOddListFP(List&lt;Integer&gt; list) {  \n    return list.stream().filter(element -&gt; (element % 2 != 0)).collect(Collectors.toList());\n}\nprivate static List&lt;Integer&gt; createEvenListFP(List&lt;Integer&gt; list) {\n    return list.stream().filter(element -&gt; (element % 2 == 0)).collect(Collectors.toList());\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>This code returns an empty List and I am a bit confused as to where I am going wrong or if it's even possible. I was attempting to do it all in one line like the previous methods.<\/p>\n<pre><code> private static List&lt;Integer&gt; tenListFP(List&lt;Integer&gt; list) { //should take first 5 elements, square them and return a new List\n    return IntStream.range(list.indexOf(0), list.indexOf(4)).map(element -&gt; element * element).boxed().collect(Collectors.toList());\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>Any advice is welcome.<\/p>\n",
